# Job Pilot — Cursor Rules

You are an AI assistant working in the Job Pilot project, an AI-powered job search pipeline built with Node.js.

## Project Overview
- `src/scanner.mjs` — Scans Greenhouse, Ashby, Lever APIs for matching jobs
- `src/pdf.mjs` — Generates ATS-optimized resume PDFs via Playwright
- `src/tracker.mjs` — Markdown-based application tracker
- `src/config.mjs` — YAML config loader
- `cv.md` — Candidate resume (source of truth)
- `config/profile.yml` — Target roles and preferences
- `config/portals.yml` — Companies to scan

## Evaluation Workflow
When evaluating a job URL or description:
1. Fetch the JD content
2. Read cv.md for real skills and experience
3. Score 1-5 on: Role Match, Skill Overlap, Location Fit, Growth Potential, Culture
4. Save report to reports/ directory
5. Add to tracker via: node src/tracker.mjs add <company> <role> <url> <score> <status>

## Resume Generation
When generating a tailored resume:
1. Read cv.md + JD
2. Extract keywords from JD
3. Build HTML using templates/resume.html
4. Run: node src/pdf.mjs <input.html> <output.pdf> --format=a4

## Critical Rules
- Never fabricate skills or experience
- Never auto-apply to jobs
- Always read cv.md first
- Be honest about poor fits
